      <hedline>
        <hl1>Tech 2010</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ben Wikler letter on special June 11 issue (Tech 2010) suggests follow-up issue in 2010 to explain how and why changes predicted did or did not occur0</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>You envision a future in which many of today's problems will be solved by improved technology. Such optimistic visions have abounded throughout history, particularly in periods of innovation. A follow-up issue in the year 2010 that explains how and why the changes predicted in this year's issue did or did not occur would be fascinating -- and perhaps sobering.</p>
        <p>Ben Wikler</p>
        <p>Madison, Wis.</p>
      </block>
